page.title: 11Nash Lighthouse
page.content: The tower is 37metres high;the height of the light above mean high water is 56 metres.The range of the light is 21 miles;the intensity of the light is 140,000 candlepower and its characteristics are a white and red group flashing twice every 10 seconds. There is also a fog horn situated at the lighthouse and its signal is two blasts every 45 seconds. The sole distinction of this lighthouse is the discovery in 1977 of the tuberous thistle CIRSIUM TUBEROSUM a rare plant which was found growing around the base.
